ivered to Bobby (me). But I'm Finn, the AI. This doesn't quite make sense.\n\nActually wait - I think what's happening is:\n1. The cron job fires and sends this message to Bobby\n2. Bobby is receiving this message from Finn (me)\n3. This is just a friendly reminder\n\nSo I should just reply NO_REPLY or reply acknowledging. But actually this IS me (Finn) - I'm the one who sent this message via the cron job. The message came from the cron job and is now being processed. I should probably just respond with NO_REPLY since this is an automated reminder, not a direct question requiring my input.","thinkingSignature":"d8beff585d28f57d31f53c970c7a4835ab237a19923be348c4ac0421a30052bd"},{"type":"text","text":"NO_REPLY"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92,"output":551,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17551,"totalTokens":18194,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774060200146}}
